title: The Great Gatsby
author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
description: A classic American novel about the Jazz Age and the American Dream, following the mysterious millionaire Jay Gatsby and his obsession with the beautiful Daisy Buchanan.

title: To Kill a Mockingbird
author: Harper Lee
description: A powerful story of racial injustice and loss of innocence in the American South, told through the eyes of young Scout Finch.

author: George Orwell
description: A dystopian novel about totalitarianism, surveillance, and the manipulation of truth in a future society.

title: The Hobbit
author: J.R.R. Tolkien
description: An epic fantasy adventure following Bilbo Baggins, a hobbit who embarks on a journey with thirteen dwarves to reclaim their homeland.

title: The Alchemist
author: Paulo Coelho
description: A philosophical novel about a young Andalusian shepherd who dreams of finding a worldly treasure and embarks on a journey of self-discovery.

title: Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind
author: Yuval Noah Harari
description: A groundbreaking narrative of humanity's creation and evolution that explores the ways in which biology and history have defined us.

title: The Psychology of Money
author: Morgan Housel
description: An exploration of the strange ways people think about money, offering 19 short stories that illustrate the psychology of money.

title: Atomic Habits
author: James Clear
description: A guide to breaking bad habits and building good ones, based on proven strategies from behavioral psychology.

title: The Art of War
author: Sun Tzu
description: An ancient Chinese text on military strategy and tactics that has influenced both Eastern and Western thinking.

title: The Lean Startup
author: Eric Ries
description: A systematic approach to creating and managing successful startups in an age when companies need to innovate more than ever.

title: The Power of Now
author: Eckhart Tolle
description: A guide to spiritual enlightenment that emphasizes the importance of living in the present moment.

title: The Seven Habits of Highly Effective People
author: Stephen R. Covey
description: A comprehensive program for solving personal and professional problems through principles-centered leadership.

title: The Da Vinci Code
author: Dan Brown
description: A fast-paced thriller that combines art, religion, and conspiracy theories in a race against time.

title: The Kite Runner
author: Khaled Hosseini
description: A powerful story of friendship, betrayal, and redemption set against the backdrop of Afghanistan's turbulent history.

title: The Subtle Art of Not Giving a F*ck
author: Mark Manson
description: A counterintuitive approach to living a good life, focusing on what truly matters and letting go of what doesn't.
